  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Research and Needs-assessment in Obalanga and Kapelebyong sub-counties</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Northern Uganda is emerging from many years of conflict. Due to years of displacement and living in camps, many people are unable to earn a living or maintain a secure livelihood. Children miss out on school, many are orphaned and some are left to bring up their younger siblings. Signpost International is researching the lives of vulnerable children in two sub-counties in Amuria District. Their research will focus on ways to support people to secure safer and sustainable livelihoods, along with assessing general health status, health facilities, schools, the water and sanitation situation and other social services. They will consult directly with local people affected by the conflict in order to better understand the problems and identify solutions. The outcome of the assessment will inform the development of a programme of action and contribute to wider awareness of the situation in this area.</narrative>
  </description>
